name: Reog Ponorogo
description: Reog Ponorogo is Indonesian dance reflects the diversity of culture from ethnic groups that composed the nation of Indonesia. Austronesian roots and Melanesian tribal dance forms are visible, and influences ranging from neighbouring Asian countries; such as India, China, and Middle East to European western styles through colonization. Each ethnic group has its own distinct dances, makes total dances in Indonesia are more than 3000 Indonesian original dances. "This Art create with manualy drawing"
